1- aptly is a swiss army knife for Debian repository management: it allows you to mirror remote repositories, manage local package repositories, take snapshots, pull new versions of packages along with dependencies, publish as Debian repository

2- aptly allows you to transistion your package environment to a new version, or rollback to a previous version.

